The paper discusses the implementation of a compressed bitmap index, which is a data structure used in database systems and search engines. This suggests that the paper could belong to the categories of Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS), Databases (cs.DB), Information Retrieval (cs.IR), and Programming Languages (cs.PL). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of SIMD instructions, which could fall under the category of Computer Architecture (cs.AR) or Cryptography and Security (cs.CR). However, since the focus of the paper is on the implementation of a data structure, the first four categories are more likely.
